summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of $2,500.00 out of the General Fund of the City of Seattle, in settlement of the claim of Herman C. Hentschke and Mary A. Hentschke, his wife, for damages to their premises at 1920 13th Avenue West, Seattle, caused by the breaking of a sewer located on 12th Avenue West, between West Howe Street and West Crockett Street, on the 10th day of February, 1916, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
